  "text": "A trace is said to be serial if every read event has the same value as the last write to the same address, and such a write always exists. [CITATION_1] A trace σ is said to be sequentially consistent (SC) iff there exists a trace σ (of the same length) such that (1) σ ↑MemEvents({p} , N, N) = σ ↑MemEvents({p} , N, N) for each p ≥ 1, and (2) σ is serial. We call such a σ a serial reordering of σ. Furthermore, σ is said to be simple SC (SSC) if there exists σ with the above two properties plus the additional property",
