      "span_text": "A trace is said to be serial if every read event has the same value as the last write to the same address, and such a write always exists.  A trace σ is said to be sequentially consistent (SC) iff there exists a trace σ (of the same length) such that (1) σ ↑MemEvents({p} , N, N) = σ ↑MemEvents({p} , N, N) for each p ≥ 1, and (2) σ is serial."
